The paper deals with the task of visual landmark recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). It also involves clustering and indexing large amounts of images, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the use of user-provided tags, which is related to natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper evaluates different methods and parameters for the pipeline, which is a machine learning task (cs.LG).
